1. ML recieves CSV file as an object and sends back CSV file as an object

2. When project boots up, ML queries the Postgresql DB for all existing users and classifies them, whenever a new user joins and surfs the site, the user gets event
counter++ each time he visits or searches a product, whenever the event counter reaches X, backend sends a single user (CSV) for classification,
ML classifies and sends back to backend.

frontend - recommendation GET recommendations?user_id=${userId}

frontend (frontpage) - recommended gets a list of recommended items for specific user (40 items)
frontend (frontpage) - popular purchases gets a list of popular purchases (the backend will do it) which are 40 items with the most views (top40)
*added rating into the product model (backend has to send the model with rating to the frontend as well)

frontend (frontpage filtering) - the frontend sends a GET to get the items with the following filters (pricerange,category,instock only)
